My father was a letter carrier for 37 years. I would not be where I am today without the sacrifices he made.

After World War II, USPS was one of the few areas of the government that employed African Americans.

It’s in their memory that I'll be voting to protect @USPS. https://t.co/B4G0xy5rc9

full_text:
When I worked in a trauma center, sometimes we’d have young patients.

The thing about young people is they have no choice but to rely on adults for advice and guidance. 

In a hospital, that trust is a matter of life or death.

Kids are not immune to COVID-19. Listen to science.

full_text:
I had a telephone town hall last night. 147 of my constituents told me they're at risk of eviction due to the expiration of their COVID benefits. 

That’s 147 too many. 

We passed legislation to address this 82 days ago. The Senate must act. The people need assistance NOW.

This is child abuse.

full_text:
Today, Donald Trump sent well wishes to Ghislaine Maxwell, who is charged with procuring underage girls to be sexually abused. 

Has he sent any well wishes to the families of the more than 140,000 Americans who have died during this pandemic?

full_text:
Anti-Semitism, whether it's overt or otherwise, is unacceptable.

Conversations of understanding are important but we also must engage in uncomfortable confrontation on this issue with our loved ones, our neighbors, and our communities.

We must fight back against anti-Semitism.

On Monday, July 13 at 2 pm ET, join our founder, @shannonrwatts, and @RepKarenBass for a conversation about how gun violence, police violence and the COVID-19 pandemic disproportionately impact Black people.

Get an email reminder: https://t.co/e3YYrNt7kS https://t.co/G01Prt0OhM

full_text: The President of the United States is not above the law. https://t.co/q3pmoosZZD

While we celebrate the progress we’ve made since, it is vital we contextualize the pain gripping the country today. 

It’s the same pain we’ve carried for 400 years. 

It’s the same yearning to be free. 

Let us march on, until victory is won.

full_text:
On Juneteenth, Trump wanted to give a speech where hundreds of African Americans were massacred.

Yesterday, he delivered remarks on sacred Native lands.

The independence promised in 1776 was not for all. It was not for those killed in Tulsa. It was not for the Sioux People.

full_text:
For Oscar.
For Tamir.
For Philando.
For Alton. 
For Atatiana.
For Eric.
For Michael.
For Breonna.
For George.

For all the names we may never know.

The House of Representatives has just passed the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act of 2020.

full_text:
Last night I had a telephone town hall about the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act.

There were more than 10 thousand constituents on the call.

This is not the time for symbolic change. This is a time for action.

full_text:
The @HouseJudiciary Committee just voted to send the Justice in Policing Act to the House Floor for a final vote. 

We need to ban chokeholds, not study them.
We need to ban no-knock warrants, not study them.

full_text:
Now is not the time to study chokeholds, it's time to ban them.

Now is not the time to study no-knock warrants, it's time to ban them.

The cries in the streets are not for symbolism, they are for substantive action.

We must pass the #JusticeInPolicing Act.

retweeted_text: “The tragic death of Mr. Floyd has galvanized the entire nation to take a look at our history, because Black Americans have actually been sadly marching for over a hundred years to bring attention to this gross injustice.” - @repkarenbass #JusticeInPolicing https://t.co/HIoV4FPKIW

full_text:
It took me many years to get over the fear of those lights coming on behind me.

It wasn't fear about getting a ticket. It was fear that my interaction with the police may result in me not surviving.

This isn't just an issue for Black men. It's an issue for Black women as well. https://t.co/s1zDO3JvdH

full_text:
The chokehold used to kill Eric Garner should be illegal. 

The warrant used to kill Breonna Taylor should be illegal. 

Putting a knee on someone’s neck for 8 minutes and 46 seconds should be illegal.

The time for change is NOW.
 
Led by @TheBlackCaucus, House and Senate Democrats have been working tirelessly to develop bold, historic legislation to:
 
🗒️Hold police accountable
❌End police brutality
☀️Improve transparency
🚨Enact structural changes 
✅Protect our communities https://t.co/BLK45PbDRY

full_text:
The Justice in Policing Act of 2020 will hold abusive law enforcement officers accountable, change the culture of law enforcement and build trust between law enforcement and our communities.

It establishes a bold, transformative vision of policing in America.

Today we act.

full_text:
George Floyd was murdered 9 days ago. 

Three police officers who helped facilitate his murder still roam free. 

Breonna Taylor was murdered 82 days ago. 

Every single one of the officers who were involved still roam free.

full_text:
How were you scared for your life as a police officer if you shot someone in the back as they were running away from you?

Police officers must be able to be held accountable and they must be able to be prosecuted. @TheBlackCaucus is working on legislation to address both issues. https://t.co/ZJwBDd5jsT

It feels like it's open season on Black folks not just because of the police murders, but because of the police brutality.

We're stopped if we're not wearing medical masks. Meanwhile, armed vigilantes are taking over the Michigan state capitol unbothered.

Where is the justice? https://t.co/W5fgVYASKu

full_text:
If you’re mad, if you’re distraught, if you’re angry, if you’re hurting: fight back against the system that killed George Floyd, don’t destroy our communities and neighborhoods. 

They want to see us burn. Don’t do their work for them.

retweeted_text:
"That is not sufficient..."

@RepKarenBass, Chair of the Congressional Black Caucus, says the 3rd degree murder arrest of Officer Chauvin is not enough. 

"Every one of those officers should be arrested & charged like any other crime."

More w @KarenBassTweets on @TheIssueIsShow. https://t.co/sQVTexgyTd

full_text:
Those who beat Rodney King never paid the price for their violence, but the violence that happened in LA in 1992 was not the answer.

The answer is action. 2/2

full_text:
100,000 people in the richest country in the history of the world have died because of COVID-19.

If we had acted aggressively and much earlier, how many of the 100,000 would be alive today?

Failed leadership.

100,000 lives.
100,000 stories.
100,000 loved ones.

Gone.

And he did. 2/

We run with Ahmaud. We stand with Bre.

Alice is a nurse on the frontlines of this pandemic. 

She should not have to wake up every day and wonder if her partner is going to die of COVID-19 in prison. https://t.co/3kkkRsuNhZ

full_text: Today marks the 105th anniversary of the Meds Yeghern and the first since Congress officially recognized the Armenian Genocide. We join in solidarity, honoring those systematically expelled and killed and are reinvigorated in our efforts to protect human rights around the world.

full_text:
The disproportionate COVID-19 infection and death rates among African Americans are manifestations of longstanding structural inequalities in this country.

Thank you @drsanjaygupta for understanding of these health disparities amongst African Americans in this country. https://t.co/uhBaikOl8y

full_text:
Some, times in our lives, 
we all have pain,
we all have sorrow;
But, if we are wise,
we know that there's,
always tomorrow.

Lean on me.

Thank you Bill Withers for your voice, your words and your songs, which remind us in the end, joy, happiness and love will transcend time. https://t.co/qxueTFfFtn

There are hundreds of thousands of immigrants in this country that are on the frontlines of this pandemic. 

They are in our hospitals, our factories, and our grocery stores. 

The latest stimulus leaves many of them out, especially our #Dreamers. 1/

It’s the beginning of the month.

Landlords in the City of Los Angeles are prohibited from evicting residential tenants during this emergency period if the tenant is unable to pay rent due to circumstances related to the pandemic.
